  "id": "sec-percent-change",
  "level": "1",
  "url": "sec-percent-change.html",
  "type": "Section",
  "number": "6.2",
  "title": "Percent Change",
  "body": " Percent Change   In , we saw:   If Audryn left a $12.25 tip on a $68.00 bill, then she left an 18% tip. She paid $80.24 in totla, or 118% of the original bill.      If August bought a shirt that originally cost $25 but was 15% off, then he paid $21.25 for the shirt. The price he paid was 85% of the original price.     We often describe increases and decreases in terms of percents.   The initial value is the original amount.    The percent change or relative change is the percent increase or decrease from the initial value. The percent change is negative if it's a decrease.    The change factor is the new value as a percent of the original value, divided by 100.      In the examples of Audryn and August, we have  Examples of Percent Change Vocabulary     Audryn  August    Initial Value  68  25    Percent Change  18%  -15%    Change Factor  1.18  0.85      The change factor is always .     The city of Denver has a 9.15% sales tax. What is the change factor for the cost of items purchased in Denver?      A store is having a sale and all of its items are 25% off. What is the change factor for the price of items in this store?        Multiply . How does your answer compare to the total Audryn paid for her dinner?      Multiply . How does your answer compare to what August paid for his shirt?      Mccoy bought a pair of earbuds in Denver for $79.99.     Find the amount they paid after sales tax.      Multiply part (a).      What do you notice about your answers?      In , you should have noticed that     In 2024, Jacob worked as a fast food manager and had a taxable income of $61,009. He paid 13.9% in federal income tax.     What are the initial value and percent change?      What is the change factor?      Use the change factor to find Jacob's income after taxes.       According to the US Census Bureau , the population of Denver County was 600,158 people in 2010. Denver County's population increased 19.4% between 2010 and 2023.     What are the initial value and percent change?      What is the change factor?      Use the change factor to find Denver County's population in 2023.       According to a local news report from August 2024 , the median rent for a two-bedroom apartment in Denver was $2,470, a 1.6% increase from August 2023.     What is the change factor for the median rent of a two-bedroom apartment in Denver from 2023 to 2024?      The news report included the median rent in 2024, but not the median rent in 2023! That is, it gave us the new value, instead of the initial value. Use the new value (given in the problem statement) and the change factor to find the initial value (the median rent in 2023).       A store advertises an Apple Watch Series 10 as on sale for $309. The ad says that this is a 28% discount from its original price.     What is the change factor for the price of the Apple Watch?      The ad includes the sales price, but not the original price. Use the sales price and the change factor to find the original price.       Celeste has $40 to pay for lunch, including tip. She always tips 21%, and wants to figure out the maximum amount that she can spend on her lunch in order to have enough to pay for both the lunch and the tip.     What is the change factor?      Is $40 the initial value or the new value?      Is the max amount that Celeste can spend on lunch the initial value or the new value?      Use the change factor and your answers to parts (b) and (c) to find the maximum amount that Celeste can spend on lunch.       The table below gives the median household income in Colorado, according to the Federal Reserve Bank of St. Louis    Median Household Income in Colorado, 2019 - 2023    Year  2019  2020  2021  2022  2023    Median Income ($)  72,500  83,780  84,950  89,930  96,640        Find the change factor from each year to next. Round to three (3) decimal places. The change factor from 2019 to 2020 has been done for you, as an example.   Annual Change Factors in Colorado Median Household Income    Years  Change Factor    2019 to 2020     2020 to 2021     2021 to 2022     2022 to 2023          Find the percent change from each year to the next in Colorado median household income. The percent change from 2019 to 2020 has been done for you, as an example.   Annual Percent Change in Colorado Median Household Income    Years  Percent Change    2019 to 2020     2020 to 2021     2021 to 2022     2022 to 2023          What do you notice? What do you wonder?        Challenge: Kaitlyn is ordering pizza. The screenshot below shows her order in the app, just before placing the order. On the previous screen, Kaitlyn chose to leave a 20% tip, and entered a code for a free pizza.   Summary of Kaitlyn's pizza order.   Subtotal of $14.28, discount of $10.79, $0.30 in taxes, $2.86 tip, total of $6.65.   Subtotal of $14.28, discount of $10.79, $0.30 in taxes, $2.86 tip, total of $6.65.        Kaitlyn's friend Brixton tells her not press the Place Order button, because there's obviously a scam involved in calculating the tip. Use what you've learned about percent change to explain why Brixton is suspicious.      There isn't actually a scam here, but:    The way the app has displayed the subtotal, discount, taxes, and tip is misleading and   The way the app calculated the tip might not align with what Kaitlyn was expecting.   Use what you've learned about percent change to figure out what the app has done, and explain it to Kaitlyn and Brixton.     "
